[{"id":"VR854690","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"direction_paragraph\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">Show all your work for each part of the question. The parts within the question may not have equal weight.</p><br/><div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an object far to the left of a concave mirror. The object is above the principle axis of the mirror. Ray 1 extends horizontally to the right from the top of the object to near the top of the mirror. Ray 2 extends downward and to the right from the top of the object to the point on the mirror where the principle axis passes through the mirror. A note indicates that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR854690.g01.svg\"/></div>\n<p class=\"passage_para\">An object is in front of a concave mirror, as shown in the figure. The object is free to be moved to any location along the principal axis in front of the mirror. Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> are two principal rays originating from the top of the object as shown, with Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> parallel to the principal axis and Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> directed toward the center of the mirror.</p>\n</div></div></div></div><div class=\"item_part part_id:A part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"A\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(a) For the following claims, <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">select</span> the one that correctly describes images formed by the mirror.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">_____ The image is real for any object location.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">_____ The image is virtual for any object location.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">_____ The image can be real or virtual, depending on the object location.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Justify</span> the claim you selected, referring to the behavior of the two principal rays shown in the figure. Do not manipulate equations in order to justify your selection.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR854690_rubric"},{"id":"VR854690","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:B part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"B\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(b) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Derive</span> an equation for the image location <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub i\"><math alttext=\"s sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span>, expressing <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub i\"><math alttext=\"s sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span> in terms of the object location <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub o\"><math alttext=\"s sub o\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi></msub></math></span></span>, the mirrorâ€™s focal length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\"><math alttext=\"f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>f</mi></math></span></span>, and physical constants, as appropriate.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR854690_rubric"},{"id":"VR854690","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:C part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"C\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(c) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Indicate</span> whether the equation you derived in part (b) is consistent with your response in part (a). <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Justify</span> your answer.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR854690_rubric"}]